                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Disputes Claims That AI Mode Will Be Default Search]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-hints-at-ai-mode-getting-more-intrusive/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/illustration-of-google-search-results-cluttered-with-icons-like-trash-bins-thumbs-down-and-warning-signs-with-a-cracked-google-logo-above-the-search-bar.png" length="535" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Google just can't stop pushing AI into search.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>It turns out Google isn't planning on making AI Mode the default for Google search anytime soon, but it came with news of more AI slop coming. This all came from rumors that started swirling after a comment from one of the company's own product leads, who works with Google AI.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 17:05:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-hints-at-ai-mode-getting-more-intrusive/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I'll Switch Phone Carriers Just to Get a Physical SIM]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ill-switch-phone-carriers-just-to-get-a-physical-sim/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/smiling_woman_using_a_smartphone_while_standing_next_to_an_oversized_sim_card_on_a_green_gradient_background.png" length="523" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mint Mobile]]></category><category><![CDATA[SIM Card]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            I'm not saying I had to, but I did. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I recently switched carriers in part to save money, but also to get my hands on a physical SIM again. After a year with eSIM, I missed having a SIM card.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 17:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ill-switch-phone-carriers-just-to-get-a-physical-sim/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Retro Tech Nostalgia: The Emotional Allure of Vintage Gadgets]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-are-we-so-nostalgic-for-retro-technology/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/shutterstock_2412987973.jpg" length="478" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tech Throwback]]></category><category><![CDATA[Retro Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Retro Computing]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Plugging right into the feels.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I guess you need to reach a certain age to have anything to be nostalgic for, but it seems that many people (myself included) are finding a paricular fascination with retro technology—either from early in your own lives, or perhaps even older than that.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-are-we-so-nostalgic-for-retro-technology/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Anker's New 7-in-1 Charging Station Is Already 22% Off]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ankers-new-7-in-1-charging-station-is-already-22-off/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/an-anker-nano-charging-station-ona-desk-with-a-phoe-while-its-usb-is-being-pulled-by-a-woman-and-man-in-a-very-unnatural-way.jpg" length="229" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><category><![CDATA[Anker Nano Charging Station (7-in-1, 100W)]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Charge all your stuff at once.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Anker Nano Charging Station is currently available for an all-time low price of <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Anker-Charging-Station-7-in-1-100W/dp/B0DFGRRV2T?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2016404&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fankers-new-7-in-1-charging-station-is-already-22-off%2F&asc_campaign=Affiliate" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim" rel="sponsored nofollow">$80 on Amazon</a>. This is an impressive 22% discount from its original price of $100. This is a great deal, especially considering it can handle all your essentials at once with its ports and outlets.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 16:20:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ankers-new-7-in-1-charging-station-is-already-22-off/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[My PC Is My Camera, and It's Now Hard to Go Back]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/my-pc-is-my-camera-and-its-now-hard-to-go-back/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/02/1000059203.jpg" length="357" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Camera]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Galaxy Z Fold 6]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            One of the challenges of working from a laptop is what's missing on the back.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>For over a year, I’ve taken photos using the same device I use for everything else—and being able to take a picture and immediately use it is, for lack of a better word, quite magical.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 16:00:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/my-pc-is-my-camera-and-its-now-hard-to-go-back/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Shake Your iPhone for AI Summaries with Firefox's New Feature]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-wants-you-to-shake-your-iphone-for-summary/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Gunther]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/firefox-logo-at-the-center-with-fire-surrounding-the-image.jpg" length="1627" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Firefox]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Intelligence]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This new feature harnesses Apple Intelligence to provide concise AI-generated summaries of webpages on your iPhone
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Firefox, the popular third-party web browser for Windows, macOS, Linux, Android, and iOS, has a fancy new feature for iPhone users. The company knows that most people browse the web on their small phone screen, so it's now rolling out a new "shake to summarize" feature powered by Apple Intelligence.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 15:34:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/firefox-wants-you-to-shake-your-iphone-for-summary/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[9 Hidden Android Features You Probably Didn't Know Existed]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/think-youre-an-android-pro-these-9-hidden-features-will-prove-you-wrong/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/android-mascot-standing-next-to-a-smartphone-with-a-robotic-arm-holding-a-message-icon-on-a-conveyor-belt.png" length="640" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><category><![CDATA[Samsung Phones & Tablets]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don’t be the last to discover these android features.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I have used both Android and iPhone, and one of the reasons I will always prefer Android is the variety of features it offers. No matter how long you have been an Android user, you will often come across a feature you may never have heard of before. With that said, here are some of the lesser-known Android features that can be really helpful in your day-to-day tasks.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 15:30:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/think-youre-an-android-pro-these-9-hidden-features-will-prove-you-wrong/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google's NotebookLM Just Got More Features]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/googles-notebooklm-just-got-more-features/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/the-new-features-of-notebooklm-being-flashcards-audio-learning-guide-quizzes-and-more-lined-up-on-a-colorful-background.jpg" length="119" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[NotebookLM]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Quiz yourself, with the power of generative AI.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>NotebookLM, Google's AI-powered research and learning assistant, has added a bunch of new features. The platform can act like a tutor now, with Flashcards, Quizzes, a redesigned Reports function, and a "Learning Guide" conversational style.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 15:14:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/googles-notebooklm-just-got-more-features/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The New Pebble Smartwatch Is Shipping This Month, But With Some Changes]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-new-pebble-smartwatch-is-shipping-this-month-but-with-some-changes/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/pxl_20250327_145226590-portrait.jpg" length="532" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Pebble]]></category><category><![CDATA[Smart Watches]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The Pebble 2 Duo is almost here, but it comes with a few unexpected compromises.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Back in March, the founder of Pebble announced the <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/pebble-is-back-with-2-new-e-paper-smartwatches-starting-at-149/" target="_blank">much-loved e-paper smartwatch would return</a>. After all these months, it's finally happening. Pebble 2 Duo is officially in mass production, and you might get to have one on your wrist this month—with a catch.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 15:13:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-new-pebble-smartwatch-is-shipping-this-month-but-with-some-changes/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[LineageOS Now Supports the OnePlus 12, Moto G Stylus 5G, and 8 More Phones]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/lineageos-now-supports-the-oneplus-12-moto-g-stylus-5g-and-8-more-phones/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/lineageos.jpg" length="170" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Android Phones & Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[LineageOS]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The Android custom ROM has added 10 more devices to its official roster since the start of August.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>LineageOS is (probably) the most popular Android custom ROM, bringing a stock-like experience and longer support to many phones and tablets. The project has recently added official support for 10 more phones, including the OnePlus 12 and original Moto G Stylus 5G.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 09 Sep 2025 15:07:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/lineageos-now-supports-the-oneplus-12-moto-g-stylus-5g-and-8-more-phones/</guid></item></channel>
